                            <comment id="13793843" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 13 Oct 2013 23:43:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=hossman_lucene%40fucit.org&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;hossman_lucene@fucit.org&quot;&gt;hossman_lucene@fucit.org&lt;/a&gt; and I have both tracked down this issue at one point or another (with no fix implemented yet). I can&apos;t recall/find the JIRA issue that might refer to this right now though.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13793844" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 13 Oct 2013 23:44:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To refresh Hoss&apos;s memory - this was related to the core reload after replication. I can&apos;t remember the details without doing some digging again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13793847" author="rcmuir" created="Sun, 13 Oct 2013 23:50:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see the core reload method failing too (doTestReplicateAfterCoreReload). But I think thats a different failure than this doTestStressReplication.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When doTestReplicationAfterCoreReload fails, the set of actual files differs from expected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When doTestStressReplication fails, its because of this: java.lang.AssertionError: timed out waiting for collection1 startAt time to exceed: Tue Aug 13 19:08:57 NFT 2013&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13793849" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Sun, 13 Oct 2013 23:54:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still think it&apos;s what I&apos;m referring too - the start time has not changed due to this core reload and it happening in the same thread or something along those lines - my memory is fuzzy, but it applies to doTestStressReplication. Hopefully Hossman remembers better than me or is willing to exercise his better research skills.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the doTestReplicateAfterCoreReload fails are probably something else and a coincidence on the name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13793906" author="hossman" created="Mon, 14 Oct 2013 04:07:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assuming this is what i think it is, i got as far as i could, and then miller said he&apos;d take a look at the weird code i found...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4709&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4709&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4629&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4629&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;...the best suggestion i had to offer (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-4709&quot; title=&quot;dir lock error if reopening cores to fast?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-4709&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-4709&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;)...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;ie: is there a bug here to fix in SolrCore; or should SnapPuller include retry logic if the core reload fails; or both? &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13828976" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Thu, 21 Nov 2013 14:36:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay, back to looking at this due to a local test failure that&apos;s driving me nuts.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now I think I remember what I was talking about - I think the issue would be solved if we didn&apos;t start a new thread to do the reload - that means it can easily happen to late for logic in the reload to work as hoped. We can make it happen like we want if we didn&apos;t start a new thread, but we can&apos;t reload a core from a core handler in the same thread - that&apos;s the issue I was referring to.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think I&apos;ve got a workaround.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
